cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of GraphSAGE, a graph neural network, by using a data-driven sampling method. The paper focuses on machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques for graph analysis, which are typically covered in the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests a potential fit for the cs.SI sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves subsampling neighborhoods, which is a common technique in graph data structures, making cs.DS a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a node classification benchmark, which could potentially fit in the cs.CV sub-category as well.
